People often don’t know which program to use or what airline to fly on to make the best use of their miles and points. There are a lot of rules that confuse people and discourage them from booking award tickets. And many are shocked when they see the taxes and surcharges levied on some of those tickets. That’s where we come in. We set out to make these programs simple enough for anyone to use. And we’ll help you track your miles and boost your balance so you can achieve your dream faster. We want to open up access to the best rewards to everyone. Full Description: Array Telepresence is enabling immersive telepresence at revolutionary price-points using existing videoconferencing codecs and standard conference room furniture.  The company has pioneered the science of Image Improvement where the company’s next generation telepresence imaging systems dramatically and measurably improve the scene before handing it off to a standard videoconferencing codec.   Array's Equal-i Technology brings the farthest participants “up-close-and-personal”, improving the eye-line to perfect vertical, improves the meeting format, conceals the camera and powers dual-displays using a single videoconferencing codec and bitstream.   The company's Immersive Everywhere capability allows Equal-i equipped systems to call dual-screen videoconferencing end-points that don't yet have Array and send a dual-screen immersive view. Array's Immersive PTZ is the industry's only solution for improving an incoming call from a standard system using a Pan-Tilt-Zoom camera even if the far side doesn't yet have Array.   Finally, the company's unique single-screen Video+Content operating mode allows participants to easily switch back-and-forth between sending dual-screen immersive and a single screen view that is vastly superior to a PTZ camera and data.  This mode improves calls going through MCUs, VMRs, and with desktop video conferencing clients like Skype4Business and Zoom.

Full Description: There are 11.7 million 18 Wheel Trucks working in the world today that get an average 5.5 Miles Per Gallon.  eTruck produces the world's first electric/hybrid deisel engine for these trucks and our system gets 14 MPG.  This is a game changer in the Trucking Industry.  Our chief engineer is one of the top electrical engineers in the world and has worked for many clients including Segway, Audi, Freitliner, and many Federal Govt Agencies. The margin for each sale is $25,000 and we currently have 2,000 orders with Memorandum's for Understanding for an additional 30,000 orders.   The system is patent pending.  We also have a great deal of international interest in licensing the technology.   The best part is that the system is completely adaptable to whatever fuel source is available.  Right now we have the infrastructure for Deisel, so that's what we're doing.  But later when the infrastructure is there, we can adapt to CNG, propane, hydrogen, etc Initially we thought that we would need to raise a great deal of money to jump start production, but we have found that our OEM's (John Deer, Marathon, etc..) have offered us excellent terms for inventory financing and our clients are willing to pay 50% of the cost up front.  Currently we are looking to raise $500,000 for operation costs to include a lease on a production facility, production employees, and legal costs for US and international patents.

Description: Aaron Andrews Apparel is an online apparel shop.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Established in the dorms of Northern Illinois University, with fellow friend and then business partner, Aaron Andrews Apparel is determined to breathe a breath of fresh air into the urban apparel, ""lifestyle"",  industry. Aaron Andrews apparel is a brand that's fundamental purpose is to motivate others to achieve their dreams. Coming from a background of community service, owner Aaron Westbrook has made it the clothing line's core value to give back to the community and to inspire youth and peers to dream big and have a clear vision to achieve goals that they set for themselves. The clothing line has motivated Aaron to be a guest speaker at various community events including the African American Heritage Board of Aurora, and to continuously lend his time to motivating students at his former middle school, Granger, in Aurora. All efforts to make a difference in the community through his business has led owner Aaron Westbrook to be acknowledged as a Phenomenal man of the year (2011) in his hometown of Aurora, and secure a nomination by his university as a Who's Who Amongst Students: colleges and universities upon graduation. Since its establishment Aaron Andrews Apparel has been featured in numerous publications including campus newspaper; Northern Star, campus magazine; Lifeline, online blogs; Stylistic Vision, Stayfreshonline, and TheGoodieBag Kingston. Many clothing companies stamp their logos on shirts with different graphic effects and call it a design... There is no underlying meaning or concept behind designs these days"" says Aaron in an interview in 2010. Though specializing in graphic T-shirts, Aaron Andrews plans to expand its collection into other facets of the industry and make the clothing line a global brand. Differentiating itself from other local and established designers, aA is motivated to making a lasting impression on fashion and in the community.

Description: Me make monster allows users to create a custom monster, then have it printed it on t-shirts, mugs, hats and other.
Full Description: Me Make Monster allows users to create a custom monster, then have it printed it on t-shirts, mugs, hats, and other products. Targeting boys 8-12 years old, Me Make Monster presents users with an interface that allows them to create a monster, changing the body parts (as well as size and position), color, skin texture, and name. Next, users save the monster and select a product type. They are then transferred to Zazzle.com. Using the Zazzle API, their monster image is seamlessly imposed upon product templates. Users can make additional modifications to the size and position of their monster image, and also select style, color, size, and other product options. They can make a purchase. In addition to ordering products, users may also download their monster image, and share it automatically on Facebook or Twitter. Future plans include adding optional account registration, which would allow users to store multiple monsters in a gallery, add them to interactive stories, online games and other activities.
